				<text>18.4.3.2 Approximate percentage relative error</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>If \(\displaystyle f={@f@}\) and \(x, y, u\) are subject to percentage relative errors of \({@error_x@}\)%, \({@error_y@}\)% and \({@error_u@}\)% respectively, find the approximate percentage relative error in \(f\).</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>First, find \(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial x}, \dfrac{\partial f}{\partial y}\) and \(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial u}:\)</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial y} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial u} = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]] [[feedback:prt2]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Now write down an expression for the percentage relative error in \(f\):</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\delta f}{f} \times 100 \simeq \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]\(\dfrac{\delta x}{x} \times 100 +\)&nbsp; [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] \(\dfrac{\delta y}{y} \times 100 - \) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] \(\dfrac{\delta u}{u} \times
    100\) </p>
<p>[[feedback:prt4]] [[feedback:prt5]] [[feedback:prt6]]</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Inputting the the percentage relative errors of \({@error_x@}\)%, \({@error_y@}\)%, \({@error_u@}\)% in \(x,y,u\), the value of the percentage relative error is [[input:ans7]] [[validation:ans7]] %.</p>
<p> [[feedback:prt7]]</p>]]></text>
