    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given \[ \displaystyle f={@f@}\] and \(x, y, u\) are subject to percentage relative errors of \({@error_x@}\)%, \({@error_y@}\)% and \({@error_u@}\)% respectively.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We are asked to find the approximate percentage relative error in \(f\).</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>First, find \(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial x}, \dfrac{\partial f}{\partial y}\) and \(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial u}:\)</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \displaystyle {@f_x@}\)</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial y} = \displaystyle {@f_y@}\)</p>
<p>\(\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial u} =&nbsp;\displaystyle {@f_u@}\)</p>
<p>Now we write down the expression of \( \delta f .\)</p>
<p>\[ \delta f&nbsp;\simeq {@f_x@} \delta x +{@f_y@} \delta y {@f_u@} \delta u \]</p>
<p>Hence we write down an expression for the percentage relative error in \(f\):</p>
<p>\[&nbsp;\dfrac{\delta f}{f} \times 100 \simeq {@f_x@} \times {@f_inv@} \delta x \times 100 +{@f_y@} \times {@f_inv@} \delta y \times 100 {@f_u@} \times {@f_inv@} \delta u \times 100 \]</p>
<p>Then we calculate the values of the percentage relative error:</p>
<p>\[\dfrac{\delta f}{f} \times 100 \simeq {@delta_x_coeff@} \dfrac{\delta x}{x} \times 100 + {@delta_y_coeff@} \dfrac{\delta y}{y} \times 100&nbsp; {@delta_u_coeff@} \dfrac{\delta u}{u} \times 100\]
</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Inputting the the percentage relative errors of \(\displaystyle {@error_x@}\)%, \({@error_y@}\)%, \({@error_u@}\)% in \(x,y,u\), the value of the percentage relative error is&nbsp; \({@percent_error@} \%.\)</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
